'''QFX Cinemas''' is a cinema chain in Nepal with cinemas in the major cities of Nepal.<ref>{{cite web|title=QFX Cinemas opens new multiplex in Pulchowk|url=http://admin.myrepublica.com/economy/story/40525/qfx-cinemas-opens-new-multiplex-in-pulchowk.html|website=Republica|accessdate=4 January 2017|ref=16}}</ref> It was founded by Rajesh Siddhi, Bhaskar Dhungana and Nakim Uddin.<ref>{{cite web|last1=Basnet|first1=Smriti|title=Team Quest’s LABIM|url=http://nepalitimes.com/article/Nepali-Times-Buzz/Team-quests-labim-mall,3097|website=Nepali Times|accessdate=4 January 2017|ref=12}}</ref> It features [[Cinema of Nepal | Nepali movies]] as well as [[Bollywood]] and [[Hollywood]] movies.<ref>{{cite web|title=Kumari Cinemas|url=http://bossnepal.com/kumari-cinemas/|website=Boss Nepal|accessdate=4 January 2017|ref=16}}</ref>
==History== QFX Cinemas started with the renovation of Jai Nepal Cinema,<ref>{{cite web|last1=GURUNG|first1=JANAKI|title=Jai Nepal|url=http://nepalitimes.com/news.php?id=5411#.WG0iZFN97IV|website=Nepali Times|accessdate=4 January 2017|ref=14}}</ref> which is the oldest cinema house in Nepal. Following the development, Jai Nepal and company revamped and launched Kumari hall. QFX Civil Mall in Sundhara is Nepal’s first most advanced [[Multiplex (movie theater)|multiplex]].<ref>{{cite web|title=QFX-Central Cinema opening at Civil Mall Sundhara|url=http://www.ktm2day.com/2010/09/24/qfx-central-cinema-opening-at-civil-mall-sundhara/|publisher=Ktm2day.com|accessdate=4 January 2017|ref=15}}</ref> After successfully operating its chain in Kathmandu Valley, QFX Cinemas opened franchise model: Bageshwori theater in [[Nepalgunj]], Jalma theater in [[Bharatpur, Nepal|Narayanghat]], Chitwan,<ref>{{cite web|last1=Nepal|first1=Anand|title=QFX theater, DCN Jalma opens in Chitwan|url=http://xnepali.net/qfx-theater-dcn-jalma-opens-in-chitwan/|website=xNepali|accessdate=4 January 2017|ref=13}}</ref> Cineplex theater in [[Pokhara]].<ref>{{cite web|title=QFX Cinemas Now in Pokhara|url=http://www.newbusinessage.com/Articles/view/4359|website=New Business Age|accessdate=4 January 2017|ref=13}}</ref> As of January 2017, the company had 15 screens in Nepal.
==Features== QFX Labim Mall in Pulchowk, [[Lalitpur, Nepal|Lalitpur]] is the first multiplex of Nepal to be equipped with a high resolution 4K digital cinema projection system.<ref>{{cite web|title=QFX Cinemas opening in Pulchowk|url=http://thehimalayantimes.com/entertainment/events/qfx-cinemas-opening-pulchowk/|website=The Himalayan Times|accessdate=4 January 2017|ref=15}}</ref> QFX Cimemas multiplex are equipped with digital projectors from Barco, a proponent of digital cinema technology.<ref>{{cite web|title=QFX-Lalitpur|url=http://kathmandupost.ekantipur.com/printedition/news/2016-03-16/qfx-lalitpur.html|website=The Kathmandu Post|accessdate=4 January 2017|ref=11}}</ref>
